# Conditional columns — when / otherwise

## The DataFrame CASE WHEN

- Chain `.when(cond, value)` per branch, finish with `.otherwise(default)`
- **Always** provide `.otherwise()` — else unmatched rows become `null` silently

## The gotcha — every branch is evaluated

- Unlike Python `if/elif`, Spark computes **every** result expression per row, then picks the match
- `when(divisor != 0, value/divisor).otherwise(0)` **does not** avoid divide-by-zero

## Two safe fixes

- Coalesce the input: `value / when(divisor == 0, None).otherwise(divisor)`
- Pull the unsafe expr into its own null-safe `withColumn`
